Analyze the following learning outcome and provide confidence scores for how well it aligns with each BYU Aim:

Title: Basic Principles and Processes of Language Change
Details: 1. be able to discuss generally the basic principles and processes of language change regarding phonological, morphological, syntactic, lexical and semantic change;

Analyze the following learning outcome and provide confidence scores for how well it aligns with each BYU Aim:

Title: Types of Language Change
Details: 2. be able to identify examples of such types of language change as they pertain to the history of the German language, e.g., assimilation, affrication, etc.;

Analyze the following learning outcome and provide confidence scores for how well it aligns with each BYU Aim:

Title: Relationship between Branches of Germanic
Details: 5. be able to describe the relationship between the three main branches of Germanic, namely Gothic, Northern Germanic and West Germanic and outline the major Germanic languages, including the West Germanic languages;

Analyze the following learning outcome and provide confidence scores for how well it aligns with each BYU Aim:

Title: Changes Distinguishing West Germanic from other Germanic Bra
Details: 6. be able to identify and describe the changes distinguishing West Germanic from other Germanic branches;

Analyze the following learning outcome and provide confidence scores for how well it aligns with each BYU Aim:

Title: Changes Distinguishing Germanic from West Germanic Languages
Details: 7. be able to identify and describe the changes which distinguished German from the other West Germanic languages as well as the changes from Old High German to Middle High German to Modern German;

Analyze the following learning outcome and provide confidence scores for how well it aligns with each BYU Aim:

Title: Main Dialects of Old High German, Middle High German, and Mo
Details: 8. be able to identify the main dialects of Old High German, Middle High German and Modern German and describe their location and distinguishing features;

Analyze the following learning outcome and provide confidence scores for how well it aligns with each BYU Aim:

Title: External Influences that Shaped the History of the German La
Details: 9. understand and be able to describe the external influences which helped shape the history of the German language, e.g., Luther's influence, Charlemagne, the printing press, grammarians, war, trade, etc.;

Analyze the following learning outcome and provide confidence scores for how well it aligns with each BYU Aim:

Title: Research
Details: 12. be able to carry out research on one aspect of the history of the Germanic languages and provide a brief and clear overview of a topic related to a change in one of the Germanic languages in both written and oral form to communicate my findings in a paper in a clear manner using primary literature (journal articles);

Analyze the following learning outcome and provide confidence scores for how well it aligns with each BYU Aim:

Title: Seeking Sources on Topics in Germanic Linguistics
Details: 13. be able to seek sources on topics in Germanic linguistics;

Analyze the following learning outcome and provide confidence scores for how well it aligns with each BYU Aim:

Title: Applying Learned Material to English and Other Languages
Details: 14. be able to make connections between what we learn in class about the history of German to better understand English, the German language and how languages (including my own language use) can change and/or differ from others' language;

Analyze the following learning outcome and provide confidence scores for how well it aligns with each BYU Aim:

Title: Identifying Supporting Quotes
Details: 15. be able to identify useful quotes that will help me support the thesis of my paper;

Analyze the following learning outcome and provide confidence scores for how well it aligns with each BYU Aim:

Title: Identifying data that Supports an Argument
Details: 17. be able to identify data that supports the arguments I am making or citing;

Analyze the following learning outcome and provide confidence scores for how well it aligns with each BYU Aim:

Title: Introducing and Citing Quotes
Details: 18 be able to introduce and cite quotes properly;

Analyze the following learning outcome and provide confidence scores for how well it aligns with each BYU Aim:

Title: Providing Adequate and Correct Citations
Details: 19. be able to provide adequate and correct citations for the points I am making or drawing on from the works of others;
